Camel case
Definition: The first word starts with a lowercase letter, and the first letter of every subsequent word
is capitalized. This can be called lowerCamelCase to be more specific.
Example: myVariableName, functionName, databaseConnection
Common use: Variables, functions, and methods

Pascal case
Definition: The first letter of every word is capitalized, including the very first word.
This is also known as UpperCamelCase.
Example: MyVariableName, ClassName, DatabaseConnection
Common use: Class names, interfaces, and types in many programming languages.